<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="545" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/934</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-03">April 3, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Japanese Ambassador called and handed me certain translations<note n="17" xml:id="d545fn17">Not printed.</note> of Japanese papers
                            regarding the recent exchange of notes between the Foreign Minister of
                            his Government and myself. They were unanimous in their favorable tone
                            and comment. I thanked him for his courtesy in bringing them to me and
                            expressed my gratification to learn of this favorable reaction in the
                            press of his country.</p>
                        <closer><signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ull</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>